doctype 5
html(lang="en")

  include head 
  style
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Rubik:wght@300;400;900&display=swap');

  body.zectr-brand
    
    include header

    section.content

      header.project-header.content-wrapper
        h1.project-title Zectr Logo and Brand
        p.project-description Logotype and Brand identity.

      section.project-overview
        div.content-wrapper
          div.info
            h1 Situation
            p At a time when I joined Zectr, my first task was to redesign existing company logo. It was done by non-professional and failed to communicate company values and direction.

          div.info
            h1 Task
            p To design a logo and a flexible brand system that would allow the brand to blossom over years. I wanted to keep the original bee, but give it a modern and tech look.
            p As a result, logo withstanded multiple company pivots from platform-to-service-to-SaaS without losing its authenticity and up-to-date feel.
          div.info
            h1 Year
            p 2017

      section.logo
        div.quarter
          img(src="img/zectr-brand/logo-1.jpg")
        div.quarter
          img(src="img/zectr-brand/logo-2.jpg")
        div.quarter
          img(src="img/zectr-brand/logo-3.jpg")
        div.quarter
          img(src="img/zectr-brand/logo-4.jpg")
        div.content-wrapper
          span.legend Official logo variation

      section.inspiration-info
        div.content-wrapper
          p.info The first Zectr logo referced a bee and a beehive hexagons. It became a starting point in my search for a new sign.
          p.info
          p.info

